[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The <xex>great</xex> or <stype>bearded bustard</stype>
(<spn>Otis tarda</spn>) is the largest game bird in Europe. It inhabits
the temperate regions of Europe and Asia, and was formerly common in
Great Britain. The <stype>little bustard</stype> (<spn>Otis
tetrax</spn>) inhabits eastern Europe and Morocco. Many other species
are known in Asia and Africa.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

